verses.roman:
śuni' mahāprabhu baḍa hailā camatkāra
prabhu kahe,--'kichu smṛti nāhika āmāra

synonyms: śuni'-hearing; mahāprabhu—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu; baḍa—very much; hailā camatkāra—became astonished; prabhu kahe—Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu said; kichu—any; smṛti—remembrance; nāhika—is not; āmāra—Mine.
translation: Hearing the description of His condition while lying near the Siṁha-dvāra, Śrī Caitanya Mahāprabhu was very astonished. He said, "I do not remember any of these things.
